  description: "abc.update_abstractmethods.__code__.co_nlocals.__class__.__name__.__eq__('int') returns True — co_nlocals is the total number of local variables; it is always a Python int; int.__class__.__name__ is 'int'; NEW in extra63: first standalone co_nlocals type identity invariant for update_abstractmethods in the abckw63 namespace; wave 234 first co_nlocals type invariant for update_abstractmethods; verified with Python 3.14.3"
